However, it is not yet won.
Congressmen must refine some details of the contract before they can make public the final form of the law and be voted.
The aid plan for the financial system will be discussed Monday in the Assembly of Representatives.
He told Reuters on Sunday, Barney Frank, chairman of the Committee for Financial Services and the Banking of the Assembly.
