The new law should also limit so-called armored contracts for directors of the companies participating in the program, and create a committee that will have control over the Fund.
This would have to be directed by the Ministry of Finance.
“We’ve worked very hard on it, and we’ve made a huge breakthrough in the direction of the agreement that will work and be effective for the market and for all Americans,” Paulson said.
The plan also counts on helping homeowners who have problems with their payments.
The government would have to agree on the new mortgage payments it purchases in order to lower the monthly burdens of debtors’ deadline payments and enable them to stay with their homes.
Marek: psychological help
The proposed plan is, according to Patria Finance chief economist David Marek, a good idea that will be realized but quite difficult.
“And that’s why we don’t know with what mechanism and at what price problematic assets will be bought.
This will be decisive for the sharing of losses between the financial sector and the government," Marek said this week for iHNed.cz server.
Whether the plan will be approved now or early next week is not, according to Marek, so relevant.
"More importantly, this week Congressmen agree on their support and give them their approval as soon as possible.
This important and psychological agreement to reach that approval is, at the moment, the most important thing,” Marek said.
