Negotiations had ended very quickly in recent hours because they feared the effect that would cause a new failure in investor mood.
The last hour they had set was the opening of markets this morning.
The two candidates in the U.S. presidential elections, who have joined the late negotiations, showed themselves rather favorable to the deal, without forgetting to express their discontent of being forced to reach this extremity.
Democratic Senator Barack Obama was given certain provisions to reach the agreement, particularly the one that would allow owners to retain their home and that on the salary of the leaders of the surviving companies by the state.
" When taxpayers are asked to take extraordinary measures because of the irresponsibility of some, we should not congratulate them.
